#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main(int ac, char *av[])
{
    char c;
    float x, y;
    int i, n;

    scanf("%d", &n);

    float min_Rx = 99999;
    float max_Rx = -99999;
    float min_Ry = 99999;
    float max_Ry = -99999;

    float min_Bx = 99999;
    float max_Bx = -99999;
    float min_By = 99999;
    float max_By = -99999;

    for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        scanf("%f %f %c", &x, &y, &c);

        if (c == 'R') // red points
        {   
            if (x < min_Rx)
                min_Rx = x;

            if(x>max_Rx)
                max_Rx = x;

            if (y < min_Ry)
                min_Ry = y;

            if(y>max_Ry)
                max_Ry = y;
        }

        if (c == 'B') // blue points
        {
            if (x < min_Bx)
                min_Bx = x;

            if(x>max_Bx)
                max_Bx = x;

            if (y < min_By)
                min_By = y;

            if(y>max_By)
                max_By = y;
        }
    }
    int flag =0;
    // case1 : checking horizontal seperation(line parallel to x axis)
    if (( max_By < min_Ry ) | (max_Ry < min_By)){
        printf("X");
        flag=1;
    }

    // case2 : checking vertical seperation(line parallel to y axis)
    if ((max_Bx < min_Rx ) | (max_Rx < min_Bx )){
        printf("Y");
        flag=1;
    }

    if(flag==0)
        printf("Not possible");

    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main(int ac, char *av[])
{

    int c,sum=0;
    int freq[10]={0}; //frequency array

    // taking input and finding sum
    while ('\n' != (c = getchar())) {
        freq[c-48] += 1;
        sum +=  c-48;
    }


    // case1 : if sum gives remainder of 1
    if(sum % 3 ==1)
    {
        //search from left
        int flag1 = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<3; i++) 
        {
            // search for {1,4,7} & decrement frquency by 1
            if (freq[(3*i)+1])
            {
                freq[(3*i)+1] -= 1;
                flag1 = 1; 
                break; 
            }
        }

        // didn't find {1,4,7}
        if(flag1 == 0)
        {
            // decrement count of {2,5,8}
            for(int i=0; i<3; i++)
            {
                int digit = (3*i)+2 ; //check for digit = {2,5,8}
                while(freq[digit] & (sum % 3) !=0 )
                {
                    freq[digit] -= 1;
                    sum = sum - digit;
                }
            }
        }        
    }

    // case2 : if sum gives remainder of 2
    if(sum % 3 ==2)
    {   
         //search from left
        int flag2 = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<3; i++) 
        {
             // search for {2,5,8} & decrement frquency by 1
            if (freq[(3*i)+2])
            {
                freq[(3*i)+2] -= 1;
                flag2 = 1;
                break; 
            }
        }

        // didn't find {2,5,8}
        if(flag2 == 0)
        {
            // decrement count of {1,4,7}
            for(int i=0; i<3; i++)
            {
                int digit = (3*i)+1 ; //check for digit = {1,4,7}
                while(freq[digit] & (sum % 3) !=0 )
                {
                    freq[digit] -= 1;
                    sum = sum - digit;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // printing lagest number with frequency array
        for(int i=9;i>=0;i--)  
        {  
            int j = freq[i];
            while(j--)
                printf("%d",i);
        }

    return 0;
}

Problem 3 :

Solution :

In[]:
#include "common.h"
#include <math.h>

int main(int ac, char *av[])
{
    int c;

    float zero_count = 0;
    float one_count = 0;
    float noise_count = 0;
    float total = 0;
    float min = 99999;
    float max = -99999;

    while ('\n' != (c = getchar())) {
        total++;
        if (c == '0')
            zero_count++;
        else if (c == '1')
            one_count++;
        else
            noise_count++;
    }
    
    if (zero_count == total | one_count == total)
        {
                min = 0;
                max = 0;
        }

    else
    {
        for(float i = 0;i<=noise_count;i++)
        {
            float p0 = (zero_count+i)/total;
            float p1 = 1 - p0;
            

            if (p0 == 1 | p1 == 1)
            {
                min = 0;
                max = 0;
            }

            float entropy = -(p0*log2(p0) + p1*log2(p1));
            if(min>entropy)
                min = entropy;
            if(max<entropy)
                max = entropy;
        }
    }
    printf("%.3f %.3f",min,max);
    return 0;
}

  • Note : While compilation , add -lm to compile using math library file

    gcc - o test3.out test3.c -lm

  • a file common.h will be present in same folder

#define matrix_alloc(mat,rows,cols,type) {                        \
    int ii;                                                       \
    type *temp;                                                   \
                                                                  \
    if (NULL == (temp = (type *) malloc(rows*cols*sizeof(type))) || \
        NULL == (mat = (type **) malloc(rows * sizeof(type *))))  \
        ERR_MESG("Out of memory");                                \
    for (ii = 0; ii < rows; temp += cols, ii++)                   \
        mat[ii] = temp;                                           \
  }

    free(mat[0]);                               \
    free(mat);                                  \
  }
